C 		  is quirky, flawed, 		  and an 		  enormous 		  success. 		  Although accidents of 		  history 		  surely helped, 		  it evidently 		  satisfied 		  a 		  need 		  for 		  a 		  system 		  implementation 		  language 		  efficient360 		  Chapter 15 		  Writing Large Programs 		  enough 		  to displace 		  assembly 		  language, 		  yet sufficiently 		  abstract 		  and fluent 		  to describe 	algorithms 	and 	interactions 	in a 	wide 	variety 	of 	environments. 	-- 	Dennis 	M. 	Ritchie.

